Pour the @water for the rice{300%ml} into a large #saucepan{} and bring to the boil. When boiling, add a @salt{pinch}, stir in the @Jasmine Rice{150%g}, lower the heat to medium and pop a lid on the pan. Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered). Leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Trim the end off the @Pak Choi{1} then chop widthways into 2cm thick chunks. Halve the @Baby Corn{60%g} lengthways. Trim the @Spring Onion{1} then thinly slice. Halve the @Red Chilli{1/2} lengthways, deseed then finely chop. Peel and grate the @Ginger{1/2} and @Garlic Clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Zest, then halve the @Lime{1}. Squeeze the lime juice into a small #bowl{}. Mix in the @Soy Sauce{12.5%ml}, @Miso Paste{15%g} and @Water{2%tbsp} for the sauce. Keep to one side.

Chop the @British Turkey Steaks{2} into 2cm chunks and sprinkle on the lime zest. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Use your hands to rub the flavourings over the turkey pieces. IMPORTANT: Remember to wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Heat a splash of oil in a large #frying pan{} over medium-high heat.

When the oil is hot, add the turkey. Stir-fry until browned, ~{3-4%minutes}. Add the baby corn and bok choy. Cook for another ~{2%minutes} before adding the garlic, ginger and half the spring onion. Stir-fry for another ~{1%minute}. Pour in the sauce, lower the heat and simmer until the turkey is cooked through, ~{2-3%minutes}. IMPORTANT: The turkey is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

Fluff up the rice with a fork. Share between your bowls and top with the stir-fry. Spoon over any sauce left in the pan and finish with a sprinkling of the remaining spring onion and some red chilli for those who want a kick. Enjoy!